                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>While attending the Council of Foreign Ministers at Moscow (March 10–April 24),
                    Secretary of State George C. Marshall had a lengthy conversation with
                    Generalissimo Stalin on the night of April 15. In addition to the discussion of
                    particular problems, the Secretary explained to Stalin that many actions by the
                    Soviet Government were having a bad effect on American public opinion and were
                    causing a deterioration in American feeling for the Soviet Union. For the report
                    of this meeting, see the memorandum of conversation of April 15, <ref
                        target="frus1947v02#pg_337">Volume II, page 337</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
